                                <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Pandnāmah-i dunyā va dīn : khāṭirat-i Amīr ʻAbd al-Raḥmān, bi-qalam-i khūdish
                                </title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt"/>
                                <title xml:lang="fa">پندنامه دنيا و دين ، خاطرات امير عبد الرحمان, بقلم خودش 
                                </title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt"/>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="desc"/>
                            <note>A fragment of the Autobiography of 'Abd al-Rahman Khan ibn Afzal Khan, Amir of Afghanistan, 1880-1901. This work of which a complete copy was 
                                formerly in the possession Sultan Muhammad Khan was planned in 10 abwabs (titles in exordium) of which the first, partly here presented, 
                                contains the autobiography, while the remainder consisted of moralising reflections and advice on the art of ruling. 
                    The present fragment covers the first 62 pages of vol.1 of Mir Munshi Sultan's Mahomed Khan's published translation The life of Abdur Rahman, Amir of Afghanistan (1900, two volumes). </note>
